STYLE GUIDES
Influenster is a forum for your thoughtful reviews, photos, videos, tips and more. Thus, we've put together these general guidelines for keeping it clean and classy here on our site:
INFLUENSTER REVIEW SECTION
Go Bare:
That’s right, bare it all. The best reviews are personal and passionate as well as open and honest. Writing a review of something you received from us? Make sure to disclose that you received the products free from Influenster for testing purposes at the beginning of your description .
Use Good Taste:
We Influensters pride ourselves on our style, so don’t trash your reputation by using offensive language and imagery. Furthermore, threats, harassment, lewdness, hate speech, and other displays of bigotry will not be tolerated.
Stay in Good Form:
Let’s save the non sequiturs for the blogosphere. We expect your contributions to be relevant to the product you’re reviewing. Reviews aren't the place for rants about political ideologies, extraordinary circumstances, or other matters that don't address the core of the consumer experience.
Cut Out the Bias:
Your contributions should be objective. Don’t review your own business or employer, your friends' or relatives' businesses, or businesses in your networking group.
Say It, Don’t Sell It:
The power of Influenster is the power of YOU. Here, consumers have the final word, so let’s not muck up our review section with more commercial noise.
Keep Secrets:
Remember the Golden Rule? Please respect the privacy of others. This means refraining from publishing personal information, close-up photos, and full names of any of your friends, enemies, and countrymen.
Innovation, Not Imitation:
What you learned in middle school still applies - absolutely NO plagiarism. We want to hear from you, so show us your (own) stuff!
Avoid the Overstatement:
It’s easy to get carried away. Please avoid exaggerating or misrepresenting your experience.
Be Picky - Click Hearts with Discretion:
These hearts don’t mean whether you “Agree.” Like reviews only when they’re useful, helpful, and truthful. Reviews are sorted by what's most helpful, so make sure new visitors see the ones that shine.
Be Constructive:
We all know how disappointing it can be when you buy something only to find it doesn’t work the way you thought it would. While it may be tempting to vent your frustrations here, remember that reviews should relay “what” and “why.” And please, for everyone’s sake, lay off the caps lock.
Be Creative:
These reviews weren’t written by robots. Let the “you” shine through!
THE Q&A SECTION
Be Curious:
Influensters have the answers. If you want to know more about a product, use the Q&A; section. But first, check that your question hasn’t already been asked. It probably has!
Share the Wealth:
Think you’ve got the answer? Help out your fellow Influensters with all the info you’ve got. Your answers should be helpful, honest, and relevant. Spread the knowledge!
*Please be advised that Influenster retains the right to remove any inappropriate content or to revoke membership for Style Guide violations.
ON YOUR BLOG, VLOG, AND SOCIAL MEDIA ACCOUNTS
Heed the VoxFox:
In all online features and comments, please make sure to disclose that you received these products complimentary for testing purposes from Influenster at the beginning of your description. This keeps everyone honest - you, us, and our partners - so we can all be trusted Influensters.
Title, Title, Title:
Don’t keep it a secret. Include the name of the product you’re reviewing in your blog or video title.
Keep it Clean:
The Influenster Facebook page is a hub for our community. Use clean language, courteous behavior, and appropriate images. Failure to do so will result in a ban from the page.
THE HUB
Stay Considerate & Constructive:
Show your fellow Influenster bloggers some love by commenting on their posts, but remember the Golden Rule - respect them as they would do for you!
Submit Quality:
Influensters value fun, quality posts and we hold the rights to decide what in Influenster Nation is appropriate or not, when specially inviting you to contribute to The Hub.
DISCLOSURE REQUIREMENT
INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS
The Federal Trade Commission requires testing program participants to disclose that they have received products for complimentary testing purposes at the beginning of all reviews, social media posts, videos and blogs as specified below. Please note that failure to abide by these rules will result in suspension from Influenster. Because no one looks good in an orange jumpsuit, we've set out the following guidelines to help keep you on the right side of the law:
Disclosure guidelines
1) VoxBox Campaigns
Blog post
Make sure to disclose that you received your products for free from Influenster and and <brand> before any text truncation. If in doubt about the character limit of the platform, make sure the disclosure is first. You may copy the following sentence: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review."
Facebook post
Make sure to disclose that you received your products for free from Influenster and and <brand> within the first 477 characters (4 lines). If in doubt about the character limit of a specific platform, make sure the disclosure is first. You may copy the following sentence: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review."
Facebook story videos
You may do a dramatic reading of the following: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review." The text needs to be displayed with in the video- it can either be typed on top of the video or it can be written on a piece of paper and displayed to the camera. You must let enough time lapse to read prompt.
Facebook story images
Insert hashtags and handles #free @Influenster @<brand> over the first image in the series.
Facebook feed videos
You may do a dramatic reading of the following: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review." You must let enough time lapse to read prompt. You should also ensure the disclosure is written in the first 477 characters (4 lines) of the caption. This text needs to be shown visually in your video as well. It can either be typed on top of the video or it can be written on a piece of paper and displayed to the camera.
Instagram feed image
Make sure to disclose that you received your products for free from Influenster and <brand> within the first 125 characters. If in doubt about the character limit of a specific platform, make sure the disclosure is first. You may copy the following sentence: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review."
Instagram feed video
You may do a dramatic reading of the following: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review." You must let enough time lapse to read prompt. You should also ensure the disclosure is written in the first 125 characters (3 lines) of the caption. This text needs to be shown visually in your video as well. It can either be typed on top of the video or it can be written on a piece of paper and displayed to the camera.
Instagram story video or IGTV
You may do a dramatic reading of the following: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review." You must let enough time lapse to read prompt. If the video is being posted on your feed, you should also ensure the text “I received these products complimentary from Influenster for testing purposes” is written in the first 125 characters of the caption. This text needs to be shown visually in your video as well. It can either be typed on top of the video or it can be written on a piece of paper and displayed to the camera.
Instagram story images
Insert hashtags and handles #free @Influenster @<brand> over the first image in the series.
Pinterest
Make sure to disclose that you received your products for free from Influenster and <brand> within the first ~125 characters (3 lines). If in doubt about the character limit of a specific platform, make sure the disclosure is first. You may copy the following sentence: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review."
Snapchat
You may do a dramatic reading of the following: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review." This text needs to be shown visually in your video as well. It can either be typed on top of the video or it can be written on a piece of paper and displayed to the camera. You must let enough time lapse to read prompt.
TikTok
Make sure to disclose that you received your products for free from Influenster and <brand> within the first 125 characters. If in doubt about the character limit of a specific platform, make sure the disclosure is first. You may copy the following sentence: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review."
Twitter
If you are posting a video, you may do a dramatic reading of the following: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review." You should also write that you received the product(s) for free from Influenster and <brand> in the description.
Youtube
You may do a dramatic reading of the following: "I received these products for free from Influenster and <brand> in exchange for my honest review." You must let enough time lapse to read prompt. You should also write that you received the product(s) for free from Influenster and brand> in the first 125 characters of the description. You may copy the sentence above into the beginning of your description.
External Reviews (with no free product sample check box)
Be sure to disclose in your review that you received the product free for testing purposes. It's important others know you received it complimentary, but do give your honest opinion-- the good, the bad and the lovely! If you can't tick a checkbox, this disclosure should be made at the top of the review to ensure that if the review is ever truncated, the full disclosure is viewable.
